INSERT INTO `holidaypackagetourplans` VALUES (1,1,'test','test','tessyt',NULL,'2022-07-07 11:17:55','2022-07-07 11:17:55'),(6,3,'More About UDUPI','Udupi Trip Package','Anytime between October and January is ideal for a visit to Udupi. The weather is warm and delightful at this time of year, and the clear sky ensures that you get the most out of your trip by participating in all of the activities available.\r\nAvoid going to the beach during the hot summer months or the monsoon season.\r\n<br><br>\r\nUdupi one-day trips are not sufficient sometimes because the place has something for everyone, including adventure seekers, heritage enthusiasts, environment lovers, beachgoers and pilgrims.\r\nBook your Udupi tourism package online for Bangalore to the Udupi tour package or other Udupi tour packages from various locations. \r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nMalpe Beach:\r\nThe Malpe beach is at the top of the list of finest beaches in India. It is located in Karnataka, 6 kilometres from Udupi. Malpe Beach\'s gorgeous white beach, agreeable weather, tasty food shacks, and sea walk make it a great destination for a brief getaway. The authorities\' most recent addition to the beach is free internet that is available 24 hours a day, seven days a week!\r\nFour rocky islands dot the broad coastline of this Karnataka hidden gem. The northernmost island is Daria-Bahadurgad, the middle island is Daria-Gadara-Kallu, and the third island is Kari-Illada-Kallu. St. Mary\'s Island, the fourth rocky island, is the most well-known and is regularly visited during Udupi\'s one-day trips. \r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\nSri Krishna Temple:\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Sri Krishna Temple, also known as Sri Krishna Matha, is a Vaishnavite temple constructed in the 13th century. This temple is notable for one particular feature: the god is worshipped via a silver-plated window and is known as the Navagraha kindi. One can easily take a bus to travel for around 5 km from Udupi Town. There is no entry fee chargeable at the entrance. Visit to connect your soul with the divine. Your Udupi trip plan must include this place.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSt. Mary’s Island:\r\n<br><br>\r\nThis is one of the 4 rocky islands of Malpe Beach. It is also known as the coconut island and it is renowned for its basalt rock formations, witnessed due to some volcanic activity millions of years ago. These unique basalt rock formations contribute to the island\'s distinct scenery, making this place a geological treasure. Home to one of India\'s 26 geological sites and remains an untouched portion of the country with enormous tourism potential. Plan your one-day trip from Udupi and explore these breathtaking places.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAnanteshwara Temple\r\n<br><br>\r\nMadhavacharya used to worship and preach Dvaita Vedanta principles in the historic temple. Lord Vishnu is worshipped here as a Shiva Linga, which is remarkable in and of itself. One of the spiritual destinations to visit during Udupi tours is the Shree Ananteshwara temple.\r\n<br><br>\r\nKaup Beach\r\n<br><br>\r\nThis beach has an antique lighthouse that was erected in 1901 and is open for visitors from 5:30 a.m. until 6:30 a.m. It is incredibly breathtaking to spend hours taking in the panoramic beauty of the sun slowly rising against the backdrop of the enormous ocean. The waters of Kaup Beach are rougher than those of Malpe Beach, yet they are nonetheless beautiful. One may have to pay a negligible amount as an entry fee. \r\n<br><br>\r\nDaria Bahadurgad Fort\r\n<br><br>\r\nDaria Bahadurgad fort is located on one of the four rocky islands of Malpe Beach. Just about 2 Km away from Malpe. The view from the fort, now mostly in ruins, is breathtaking downright, and the ideal time to visit is after sunset when the horizon turns various hues of shades of pink and orange. Udupi\'s one-day tour package can now be easily booked online at Tejas Travels. You will find the Udupi package tour inclusive of several features. \r\n<br><br>\r\nMattu Beach\r\n<br><br>\r\nMattu Beach, one of the state\'s quietest spots, is also famed for its bioluminescence at night.\r\nThe water sparkles and emits bright light in the dark due to the bloom of a microbe called Noctiluca, which emits this bioluminescence when disturbed.\r\nRelax under the clear star-studded skies arching overhead and the sea shimmering like pixie dust at your feet! It is located about 10 Km from Udupi and has no entry fees. \r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\nKarkala\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\nKarkala is dominantly populated by people who follow Jainism and is home to a 41.5-foot-tall statue of Gomateshwara, also known as Lord Bahubali. \r\nThe Western Ghats attribute Karkala with greenery all year and contains a great number of lakes. The Mahamastakabhisheka ceremony is held here, in which hundreds of Jain worshippers bathe the Bahubali sculptures with saffron, milk, honey, sandalwood, turmeric, and vermilion.\r\n\r\n<br><br>',NULL,'2022-07-07 11:40:23','2022-07-07 11:40:23'),(37,2,'2 Days and 2 Nights','A Transportal To Historic Times In Hampi','The ancient remains are an amazing site to witness for both pilgrims and tourists alike. A place of such majesty and opulence is certain to have a rich cultural legacy.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe mountainous topography enhances the historical aura of this location, attracting holidaymakers to participate in a variety of thrilling activities in addition to sightseeing. \r\nIf you are planning a journey to Hampi, the winter months of October to February is the best time to visit Hampi because many Hindu religious festivities are held.\r\n<br><br>\r\n*Temperatures (12°C to 20°C) are also good at this time. During the summer (March to June), the climate in Hampi is typically hot and humid, with temperatures reaching 41°C.\r\n<br><br>\r\nTourist Attractions:\r\n<br><br>\r\nIn the third century BC, Hampi was a component of the Mauryan Empire.\r\nHampi tourist attractions are mentioned here:',NULL,'2022-08-20 08:04:02','2022-08-20 08:04:02'),(38,2,'Day 1','Vittala Temple Visit','Vittala Temple Visit is one of Hampi\'s main places to visit, devoted to the Hindu God Vittala, a manifestation of Lord Vishnu. Vittala Temple has 56 melodic columns or musical pillars. A stone-made chariot in front of the temple\'s entrance adds to the temple\'s splendour.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Vijaya Vittala Temple doors are open from 8:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m without any admission fees.',NULL,'2022-08-20 08:04:02','2022-08-20 08:04:02'),(39,13,'GREEN VALLEY VIEW','Kodaikanal Tour Packages','The Green Valley View, formerly known as Suicide Point, provides a stunning view of the plains, deep valleys, and hills. The breathtaking vista of the Vaigai Dam is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.\r\n<br><br>\r\nKODAI LAKE\r\n<br><br>\r\nKodaikanal Lake is a man-made lake in Kodaikanal, commonly known as Kodai Lake. Vera Levinge was the guy responsible for the lake\'s ingenuity, British and early missionaries from the United States of America made this lake and is situated in the heart of Kodaikanal. \r\n<br><br>\r\nTHALAIYAR FALLS\r\n<br><br>\r\nThalaiyar Falls, also known as Rat Tail Falls, is nestled on the lush green slopes of the Palani Hill ranges in the Dindigul District of Kodaikanal. With a height of 297 metres, it is the tallest waterfall in Tamil Nadu and the sixth highest waterfall in India. There is a lookout tower in the park at Dum Dum Rock. There is a hiking trail near the waterfall.\r\n<br><br>\r\nDOLPHIN’S NOSE\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Dolphin\'s Nose is around 12 kilometres from Coonoor and is 1,500 metres above sea level. The tip of the peak of this massive rock resembles a dolphin\'s nose, and it is one of the most popular tourist destinations because there are massive canyons on both sides and there is a clear view of Catherine Falls.\r\n<br><br>\r\nPILLAR ROCK\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Pillar Rocks, located in the \'Princess of Hill Stations,\' Kodaikanal, have become a popular picnic destination. The location is called by three vertically positioned stones that reach a height of 400 feet, forming a lovely small garden. The aura here is filled with love and is proof of a wonderful love tale.\r\n<br><br>\r\nKODAIKANAL PINE FOREST\r\n <br><br>\r\nThe pine forest is one of Kodaikanal\'s protected beauties that will captivate guests with its ambience. It is Mother Nature\'s gift to those who enjoy nature photography.\r\n <br><br>\r\nTHE CROAKER’S WALK\r\n <br><br>\r\nCoaker\'s Walk in Kodaikanal is about 600 metres from the bus stop. Every day tourists can visit Coaker\'s Walk. To admire the landscape, there is an observatory with a telescope halfway along the hike.\r\n<br><br>\r\nKodaikanal is a great spot to get away from the stresses of city life, and this hill station allows you to reconnect with nature as you ride your bike or hike through the huge forests that surround the town.',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:37:54','2022-08-20 11:37:54'),(40,12,'Let the adventure begin:','Munnar Tour Package','* Kerala - travel plan has always been a major tourist destination. Kerala tour packages with the price are available on the website of Tejas Travels.\r\n* Book your Kerala trip honeymoon holiday package for a couple of tour packages from the best travel agency.\r\n* Munnar tour package for a couple for 2 days or 3 days as Munnar holiday package and Munnar travel package can be booked easily.\r\n* Plan your Munnar trip with us and get the best Munnar family tour packages from Bangalore.\r\n<br><br>\r\nKALARI KSHETRA\r\n<br><br>\r\nKalari Kshethra is the birthplace of Kalarippayattu, the oldest form of martial arts, and Kathakali, the ancient style of Indian classical dance. Kalarippayattu is commonly referred to as the \"Mother of Martial Arts,\" as it is the root from which current hand fighting systems such as Kung-Fu and Karate have grown through time.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nMUNNAR TEA PLANTATIONS\r\n<br><br>\r\nThese magnificent Tea plantations in Munnar situated many feet above sea level and boasting of the hazy sky above and green-carpeted plains below, are a must-visit for every tourist. Tea estates strewn across wide swaths of the country are guaranteed to entice you with their seductive beauty and charm.\r\n<br><br>\r\nPOTHUMEDA VIEWPOINT\r\n<br><br>\r\nPothamedu View Point, located 5 kilometres from Munnar, is surrounded by beautiful green slopes and sweeping hills. The amazing panoramic vistas of the area\'s tea, coffee, and cardamom plantations may be seen. It is an excellent location for viewing spectacular sunrises and sunsets. On a clear day, the Idukki Arch Dam, which is around 60 kilometres away, may be seen from this vantage point.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIDUKKI DAM\r\n<br><br>\r\nWith a capacity of 780 MW, the Idukki hydroelectric plant is the largest of its kind in the state. It is one of the world\'s highest 10 arch dams and the third highest in India after the Tehri Dam in Uttarakhand and the Bhakra Nangal Dam in Gujarat (Himachal Pradesh). The view is breathtaking given to the rich flora and fauna in the vicinity.\r\n<br><br>\r\nANAMUDI HILLS\r\n<br><br>\r\nAnamudi Mountain Munnar is the tallest peak in South India, rising 2,695 metres above sea level in Kerala\'s Idukki District. Anamudi peak may be reached via Eravikulam National Park in Munnar, and the icy summit can be seen on either of the Marayoor or Udumalpet roads in Munnar.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe term \'Anamudi\' means \'elephant hair,\' and it is said that the peak earned its name after some elephant hairs were discovered here.  As one of the highest peaks in India, Anamudi is a popular tourist site in Kerala.\r\n<br><br>\r\nPONMUDI DAM\r\n<br><br>\r\nPonmudi is a lovely tiny village in Trivandrum, Kerala, nestled in the lap of rolling hills of the Western Ghats, surrounded by tea plantations, lush green hills and valleys, and waterfalls and streams. The most popular activity is trekking and mountain climbing on Agasthayarkoodam, the tallest peak in the area.\r\n<br><br>\r\nTREKKING AT PONMUDI\r\n<br><br>\r\nPonmudi is a trekker\'s delight with several gorgeous paths. Trekkers might like the routes in Varayattumotta, Chinnappulle, and Braemoor, which are guided and arranged by Ponmudi Forest Protection Samithi.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nSprawling tea plantations surround the tranquil hills of Munnar, attracting adventure seekers looking for paragliding, climbs to Anamudi (South India\'s highest peak), and walks starting at the convergence of three mountain streams.  Eravikulam National Park, approximately 10 miles away, is home to colourful fauna, including the endangered Nilgiri Tahr (ibex), and 120 bird species.',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:38:55','2022-08-20 11:38:55'),(41,11,'EXPLORE THE GREAT WILD AT DANDELI:','Dandeli Holiday Packages','If Dandeli holiday packages are what you are looking for, kindly log in to Tejas Travels to find exciting offers for the best Dandeli honeymoon package and Dandeli new year packages.\r\n<br><br>\r\n*Plan a Dandeli trip with friends and explore Dandeli holiday tour packages and book a Dandeli trip.\r\n<br><br>\r\nKAVAL CAVES\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe limestone caverns are around 25 kilometres within Dandeli\'s base camp. These limestone caverns are deep into the forests of Dandeli about 20 km from the base camp. They are thought to have developed as a consequence of volcanic activity many years ago. The cave is so tiny that one must crawl in at several spots.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSKYES POINT\r\n<br><br>\r\nSykes Point, named for a British engineer, is a well-known city overlook. Tourists come to see the breathtaking top view of the Dandeli Valley covered in lush woods, to study various exotic species in their native habitats, and to watch the convergence of the rivers Kali and Nagzari. The 12-km hike down the river from Kulgi through lovely green woodlands to Syke\'s point.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMOLANGI\r\n<br><br>\r\nMolangi is a wonderful camping spot. The location is around 11 kilometres from Kali\'s Wilderness Camp and is deep in the lush forest. The Kali River carved its way through the rocks, cliffs, and slopes.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSYNTHERI ROCKS\r\n<br><br>\r\nA 300ft monolith granite rock is located around 30 km from the Kali wildlife camp, beside the rushing waters of the river Kaneri. Because of erosion, the rock has some hollow spots in it.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSHIROLI PEAKS\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe summit is the highest point in the region, from where one can see the majestic Sahyadri Mountains.\r\n<br><br>\r\nDandeli is a hub for River rafting, zip line, kayaking, nature walks and more.\r\nDandeli adventure package trip is all-inclusive and is suitable for 2 nights, 3 days package, a 1-day package or 2 days package.',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:39:37','2022-08-20 11:39:37'),(42,10,'ASTONISHING BEAUTY OF GOA:','Goa Tour Package','Goa trip is like a dream trip for many. The beautiful clean beaches and lovely Goan food and several tourist destinations make the Goa tour package a complete one.\r\n<br><br>\r\n Goa trip packages from Bangalore are perfect for solo travel as well as with your family. \r\n<br><br>\r\nOur Goa trip planner packages have several options for Goa tours and travel from Tejas Travel’s website.\r\n<br><br>\r\nGoa holiday package for a couple for 3 days from Bangalore for tour places is always on demand.\r\n <br><br>\r\nBASILICA OF BOM JESUS CHURCH:\r\n<br><br>\r\nThis world-renowned monument depicting the history of Christianity in India is a Baroque architectural masterpiece that was finished in 1605. The UNESCO World Heritage Site is approximately 400 years old and features St. Francis Xavier\'s tomb.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nCANDOLIM BEACH\r\n\r\nThe bulk carrier \"River Princess,\" which went aground 100 m off Candolim Beach, is one among the more remarkable sites. Don\'t miss the Aguada Fort while visiting Candolim Beach. The Portuguese constructed the fort in 1912 to defend against Dutch and Maratha invasions.\r\n\r\nCALANGUTE BEACH\r\n\r\nCalangute, sometimes known as the \"Queen of Beaches,\" is Goa\'s most famous beach. It is also the most touristic of all Goan beaches. Calangute beach attracts visitors and travellers from all over the world due to its high popularity, and the beach is often crowded. The coastline is dotted with shacks, and several of the clubs open directly into the beach. On the beach, there are several concerts, including rock and pop beat shows, open-air dances, and fetes.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nBAGA BEACH\r\n<br><br>\r\nBaga (Beach) is a literal extension of Calangute and is one of Goa\'s most popular and busy beaches. Baga is smaller than the beaches on each side of it, Calangute and Colva. It is popular with tourists who wish to sunbathe in tranquilly during the day and enjoy Goa\'s nightlife at night. Baga, on the other hand, maybe just as fascinating for the more energetic traveller, with a variety of water activities ranging from jet skis to paragliding.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAGONDA BEACH\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe beautiful ivory-coloured cove of Agonda is renowned as \"the silent beach,\" so it\'s no surprise that it\'s a popular destination for restful retreats! Surrounded by lush flora, the molasses-paced community redefines the passage of time, ideally extending your get-away-from-it-all vacation. Stay in a lovely beach bungalow and let your concerns go away.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAGUADA FORT\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe majestic Fort of Aguada, located 4 kilometres from Candolim, was built to prevent ships from entering the River Mandovi, thereby safeguarding old Goa from raids by Dutch and Marathas. Aguda Fort is a popular Goa tourist attraction and one of the state\'s important historical sites. Aguada Fort is one of the must-see sights in Goa.\r\n<br><br>\r\nRIVER CRUISE MANDOVI\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Goa Tourist Department also arranges a full-day (9.30 AM to 4 PM) backwater cruise trip from Santa Monica. The Backwater Cruise travels along the Mandovi River\'s mangrove-lined banks between the Chorao and Divar islands, including Dr Salim Ali\'s Bird Sanctuary.\r\nOffshore casino ships in Goa may be reached from Panaji Jetty, just before Santa Monica Jetty charging  Rs. 300 per person. The backwater cruise is slightly on the higher end.\r\nSupper Cruise (2 Hours - Wednesday and Saturday): Rs. 650 per person, including dinner (Rs. 300 for children between 5-12 years)\r\n<br><br>\r\nDUDHSAGAR WATERFALLS\r\n<br><br>\r\nDudhsagar Falls is Goa\'s largest and tallest waterfall, located 71 kilometres from Panjim Kadamba Bus Stand, 50 kilometres from Margao Railway Station, and 10 kilometres from Kulem. It is one of the must-see Goa tourist attractions and is frequently included in Goa tourism advertising. Another prominent destination not to be missed on a Goa travel package is Dudhsagar Falls.\r\nDudhsagar means \"Sea of Milk\" in Konkani and gets its name from its appearance as an overflowing sea of milk. It is a four-tiered waterfall with various routes to each level. Locals refer to the waterfall as Vajra Sakala Falls, although most people refer to it as Tambdi Surla Falls because of the renowned hiking track that begins at Tambdi Surla Mahadev Temple.\r\nThe waterfall was originally the home of a lovely princess, according to mythology. \r\n\r\n<br><br>',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:40:07','2022-08-20 11:40:07'),(43,9,'MUST-VISIT SITES FOR COORG TRAVEL- SCOTLAND OF INDIA','Coorg Tour Packages','This location offers a continuously misty landscape and a popular coffee plantation. \r\n<br><br>\r\nTo enjoy the view, people prefer booking cabs from Mysore to Coorg. Also, Coorg packages from Bangalore for 2 days are yet another popular choice.\r\nBudget packages to travel to Coorg with family to make your vacation budget-friendly, you have to choose the Coorg package from Bangalore from Tejas Travels.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMysore to Coorg bus rides, Bangalore to Coorg by car hire,  and Coorg tour packages, and Bangalore to Madikeri tour packages for Madikeri are available on the online portal through Tejas Travels.\r\n<br><br>\r\nTALAKAVERI\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe source of the Kaveri- a tranquil birthplace of a tremendous river- is located in the Bhramagiri Hills. At a height of 1276 metres above sea level, it also boasts a modest temple that is frequently visited by pilgrims during their Coorg travel or Mysore Coorg tour package.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMADIKERI FALLS\r\n<br><br>\r\nMadikeri tourism is well-known. The beginning of Kaveri and the most beautiful waterfalls are located between coffee plantations and spice fields. There are several tall trees with pepper vines entwined around them. The fresh air with all of these aromas might transport you to a higher degree of relaxation. Don\'t miss the Madikeri fort tour for an unforgettable experience.\r\n<br><br>\r\nDUBARE ELEPHANT CAMP\r\n<br><br>\r\nDubare Elephant Camp is located on the banks of the Kaveri River in Karnataka\'s Coorg district. The camp is a prominent tourist destination that draws visitors from all over the world, particularly wildlife enthusiasts from Bangalore to Coorg and other places. It allows guests to get close to elephants and participate in numerous elephant-related activities enriching Madikeri tourism.\r\n<br><br>\r\nHONNAMANA KERE\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Lake also has stunning scenic splendour. It is a place where people can unwind and spend quality time with their loved ones. It is bordered by mountains, cliffs, and vast swaths of coffee plantations, as well as two hills, known as Gavi Betta and Mori Betta. Along with sightseeing, one can participate in a variety of outdoor sports such as boating and fishing making this an interesting Madikeri tourist place.\r\n<br><br>\r\nBRAHMAGIRI HILLS\r\n<br><br>\r\nBangalore to Madikeri tour package generally includes a visit to Brahmagiri Hills. Brahmagiri is a hill next to the Talacauvery temple.  The hillock\'s gates open at 10 a.m. and close at 4 p.m. It takes around 45 minutes to go up and down. Regardless of which direction one looks, the view from here is spectacular. The beautiful Western Ghats may be seen on borders adjacent to the hill, as well as the Talacauvery temple, which is the source of the Cauvery River. This location is ideal for photographers and selfie fanatics.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMANDALPATTI TREK\r\n<br><br>\r\nThere are several tourist attractions in the Coorg area, and Mandalpatti, though not widely known, attracts visitors all year. Mandalpatti trip is one of the most unique and gorgeous hiking trails in the Western Ghats, with luscious green shola grasslands. Feel the excitement run through you as you begin your ascent to the summit of Mandalpatti Peak while admiring the picturesque splendour of nature. Trek to the summit and fall in love with the magnificent foliage that extends beyond the picturesque horizon. It is ideal to visit between November and January. Fact that the area is shrouded in mist at this time of year, Mandalpatti provides a gorgeous environment. The view from the summit of Mandalpatti will take your breath away. \r\n<br><br>\r\nRAJA’S SEAT\r\n<br><br>\r\nRaja\'s Seat, literally \"King\'s Seat,\" is one of Coorg\'s most prominent tourist sites. Raja\'s Seat was built for the King of Coorg and his close friends to enjoy the mountain range views of his kingdom and the sunset. Raja\'s seat provides a panoramic view of the Coorg countryside\'s mountain ranges.\r\n<br><br>\r\n This famed coffee-producing hill station is well-known not only as a renowned tourist destination due to its culture and people, The Kodavas, a local martial arts clan, are especially well-known for their warm hospitality.',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:40:28','2022-08-20 11:40:28'),(44,8,'UNLOCKING ADVENTURES','Bangalore to ooty package','Located at a lovely altitude of  2,240 m above sea level. Temperatures of Ooty have average highs ranging from 17°C to 20°C and average lows ranging from 5°C to 12°C. \r\n<br><br>\r\nOoty gets roughly 105cm of rain per year on average, with the rainy season being relatively chilly, humid, and windy. From January through March, the city has a distinct dry season perfect for your Ooty tour.\r\nThis city is a beautiful hill station in the Nilgiri Hills, which translates to \"blue mountains.\" Ooty is quite cool all year and has a plethora of interesting activities perfect for your Ooty honeymoon packages from Bangalore. \r\nThere are lakes, natural parks, and other attractions in this area that are a part of Ooty sightseeing packages.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nTOY TRAIN RIDE\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Nilgiri Mountain Railway (NMR) is a world heritage train that draws a large number of tourists to Ooty. The Nilgiri Mountain Railway, often known as the Toy Train or the Nilgiri Passenger, runs daily between Mettupalayam and Ooty, covering a distance of 26 kilometres and passing over 208 curves, 16 tunnels, and 250 bridges and takes approximately 4 to 5 hours. The train departs from Mettupalayam railway station and travels to Lovedale, and ultimately Ooty, also known as Udhagamandalam railway station. Your Ooty trip plan will be memorable riding on this train.\r\n<br><br>\r\nBOTANICAL GARDEN AND ROSE GARDEN\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Government Botanical Garden, located on the lower slopes of the Doddabetta mountain peak, is a well-kept garden measuring around 89,000 square metres. The Government Rose Garden is a major tourist destination and one of India\'s largest rose gardens and is located on the lower slopes of Elk Hill in Vijayanagaram, Ooty, at an elevation of about 2200 m. This lovely garden is 4 hectares in size and the visit is included in Ooty honeymoon packages.\r\n<br><br>\r\nDOLPHIN’S NOSE VIEWPOINT\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Ooty package is one of the most popular tourist spots in Tamil Nadu\'s Nilgiris district. The Dolphin\'s Nose is around 12 kilometres from Coonoor and is 1,500 metres above sea level. The tip of the peak of this massive rock resembles a dolphin\'s nose, and it is one of the most popular tourist destinations because there are massive canyons on both sides and there is a clear view of Catherine Falls. Bangalore to Ooty package can be booked directly from our website. \r\n<br><br>\r\nDODDABETTA PEAK\r\n<br><br>\r\nIf you leave Doddabetta Peak off your schedule, your Ooty package with your family could be an incomplete one. With a height of 2637 metres, this is the highest mountain peak in the famed Nilgiri Range, kissing the sky and standing mighty. Getting to the highest point in the area allows you a spectacular view. In addition, the Tamil Nadu Tourism Development Corporation has built a \"Telescope house\" for a greater view. Doddabetta Peak is a wonderful spot for shoots, as well as leisurely travellers who prefer to sit back and soak in the atmosphere.\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\nPYKARA LAKE\r\n<br><br>\r\nYou should book your Ooty trip from Bangalore to visit Pykara Lake. Pykara Lake is a tourist attraction that is situated Pykara Lake, around 20 kilometres from Ooty, is a renowned tourist destination. Pykara is the largest river in the Nilgiris District, flowing from the Mukurthi peak through the hilly terrain to the plateau\'s edge, where it flows over a series of waterfalls and multiple dams contributing to the hydroelectric power plant. \r\n<br><br>\r\nBHAVANI LAKE\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Mysore Ooty package must include a visit to the famous Bhavani Lake. Ooty tour packages from Bangalore have this included and is never disappointing. Bhavani Lake is one of Ooty\'s restricted regions, accessible only by Forest Department vehicles. The lake boasts crystal pure blue water and is without a doubt one of the top things to do in Ooty in June. The journey begins after the Avalanche checkpoint.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nKOTAGIRI TREK\r\n<br><br>\r\nLet us reconnect with the roots of raw nature by camping, viewing the gorgeous sunset, and stargazing through Ooty tour packages. The Kotagiri Trek, which is surrounded by lush green trees, is the ideal combination of nature and tranquillity. A typical forest route winds through clear water lakes, silken waterfalls, and a plethora of tree plantations. It is distinguished by a high level of plant diversity, exotic animal species, and two endangered species, the Lion-Tailed Macaque and the Nilgiri Tahr making your Ooty travel package for 2 days too, worthwhile.',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:41:12','2022-08-20 11:41:12'),(45,7,'FASCINATING FACTS','Chikmagalur Tour Packages','<br><br>\r\nOne of these fascinating ancient stories states that the city was offered as a dowry to King Rukmangada\'s younger daughter. As a result, the name Chikmagalur derives from the Kannada phrase \"Chikkamagala Uru,\" which means \"Younger daughter\'s town.\" The oldest daughter was granted the other section of the city, Hiremagalur ( now part of Chikmagalur).\r\n<br><br>\r\nIt is said that the first coffee harvest was planted in the Baba Budan Giri Hills around 1670, after Baba Budan discovered coffee, he brought some Yemeni coffee beans to bring the aroma of coffee to the country. This was the beginning of the Indian coffee business.\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\nCHIKMAGALUR TOURISM PRESENTS:\r\n<br><br>\r\nRIVER HEMAVATHI\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe River Hemavathi, which flows from the Ballala Rayana Durga in the Chikmagalur district, adds to the splendour of the Western Ghats. The river travels for 245 kilometres before joining the River Kaveri. It is regarded as one of Kaveri\'s major tributaries and is one of the major tourist attractions here.\r\n<br><br>\r\nBHADRA WILDLIFE SANCTUARY\r\n<br><br>\r\nOver 250 bird species can be seen, the majority of which are indigenous to the Western Ghats. The reserve also offers a 3.5 Km long nature trail at Muthod.\r\nBecause it is a Tiger Reserve, 30 Tigers and 20 Leopards can be seen in Doddahadlu and Chandanahadlu. Bhadra reservoir provides boating safaris. Timings are from 6:30 am to 8:30 am and 4:00 pm to 6:00 pm. The jeep riddle rentals may vary from Rs 400 to Rs 600 in seasons. Bus or Canter facilities are also available. \r\n<br><br>\r\nKUDREMUKH NATIONAL PARK\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Kudremukh National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, is well-known for bird watching and trekking. It is home to around 200 different bird species. To trek to Kudremukh Peak, a forest ranger permit is required.\r\nThe name Kudremukha translates to \"horse-face,\" from Kannada, referring to the park\'s highest mountain peak, which resembles the face of a horse from one side.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMULLAYANAGIRI\r\n<br><br>\r\nIt is the tallest peak between the Nilgiris and the Himalayas, providing travellers with a serene retreat is this summit with a tranquil atmosphere and natural beauty, and is ornamented with verdant grassland and coffee farms. A decent walk path is also popular among adventure seekers  particularly trekkers, as it is studded with ideal trek tracks. Sarpadhari, a steep trail, serves as the starting point for this 4 km walk. Other activities include mountain biking and road biking. \r\n<br><br>\r\nBHADRA DAM\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Bhadra dam is built on the Bhadra River, which is a tributary of the Tungabhadra River. The dam is excellent for kayaking and boating and is surrounded by lush flora. \r\nMany small islands along the river are home to migratory species such as the red spurfowl, emerald dove, black woodpecker, and green imperial pigeon.\r\n<br><br>\r\nHIREKOLALE LAKE\r\n<br><br>\r\nHirekolale Lake has risen to prominence, becoming a popular destination for tourists. The lake\'s attractiveness is enhanced when visited around sunset when the saffron colour of the sunrays is reflected, making the place appear mystical.\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe most in-demand travel seen over the last decade for short trips is Bangalore to Chikmagalur. Chikmagalur trip should be a must on your next travel destination from Bangalore.',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:41:39','2022-08-20 11:41:39'),(46,6,'ADVENTURES UNLIMITED AT MYSORE','Mysore Tour Package','Mysore trip is a must for those who live near Bangalore and can take a Mysore tour package. Road connectivity is great and has many ways of approaches.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMysore’s one-day trip will fit in perfectly during short and intermediary holidays with family and friends.\r\n<br><br>\r\nA one-day trip to Mysore is enough to cover several tourist places because the main spots are located close by.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe pleasant weather and less congested roads in Mysore will keep your travel stress-free.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMYSORE PALACE\r\n<br><br>\r\nMysore Palace was originally the home of the Wodeyar dynasty rulers of Mysore, who ruled for seven centuries. The palace is one of the largest in India, having over 2.5 million tourists each year. It is a remarkable masterpiece due to its great architecture and meticulous craftsmanship. The entrances and corridors, the portraits of kings and queens, the chariot, and the weaponry transport you to an era of the past. The grandeur of the flooring and ceiling is all a display of intricate handiwork. The palace is lit with approximately 98000 light bulbs during Dasara Festival.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nBRINDAVAN GARDENS\r\n<br><br>\r\nBuilt across the majestic Kaveri river, these beautiful gardens were constructed by Krishnaraja Wodeyar. These sprawling gardens are spread out over 60 acres and were modelled after the Shalimar Gardens of Kashmir. The beauty of these gardens is amplified even further after sundown when a host of fountains start to light up in various hues and further transform this already captivating locale into a magical place where you can be sure to fall in love purely on sight.\r\n<br><br>\r\nLALITH MAHAL\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe palace is located at the foot of Chamundi Hills and offers a spectacular view of the hills surrounding its location. Also, a part of the palace has been converted into a heritage hotel and it’s being managed by India Tourism Development Corporation (ITDC). Make sure you make a trip to see these magnificent interiors ornamented with Belgian crystal chandeliers and Persian carpets.\r\n<br><br>\r\nJAGMOHAN PALACE\r\n<br><br>\r\nJaganmohan Palace was built to serve as a royal family dwelling, but it was eventually converted into an art gallery. Many significant antiques and artworks from South India are housed at the gallery. Famous Indian artists\' works, such as Raja Ravi Verma\'s oil paintings are housed here. The art gallery also features antiques and some exquisite masterpieces.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nKARANJI LAKE\r\n<br><br>\r\n It is a picturesque destination for all bird enthusiasts and wildlife aficionados. The largest lake in Karnataka, covering several acres, is one of the most beautiful tourist attractions in Mysore. Karanji Lake, located at the foot of the Chamundi hills, has nature\'s gorgeous scenery. In addition, the lake\'s feature is that one will find an abundant number of birds which is estimated to be 70 species.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMYSORE ZOO\r\n<br><br>\r\nOne of the best zoological gardens in India is Sri Chamarajendra Zoological Gardens, better known as the Mysore Zoo. This zoo, in addition to housing diverse kinds of birds, animals, and reptiles, also engages in breeding programs for exotic and endangered species. There are several adoption programmes for these innocent animals and the names of the patrons are mentioned on display. New enclosures are added recently for orangutans. Enjoy the buggy rides if you do not wish to walk for about 3.4 km across 16 acres of total land.\r\n<br><br>\r\nWAX MUSEUM\r\n<br><br>\r\nMelody World Wax Museum, with a music theme, is a popular tourist attraction in the city. The building of this museum is estimated to be more than 90 years old and is a Mysore heritage building. This museum\'s main attractions include life-size wax sculptures dressed in native clothing playing various instruments. It also claims to have the most extensive collection of musical instruments in Karnataka and from various sections of the country and eras have been presented here.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nCHAMUNDI HILLS AND CHAMUNDESHWARI TEMPLE\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Chamundeshwari Temple, named after the Goddess Chamundi, is located atop the main hill. The main hill itself has a 1,008-step stone stairway ascending to its peak. A 7.6 m long bull Nandi carved from a single block of black granite may be observed mid-way. Tourists can enjoy a breathtaking panoramic view of the city. The Temple is built in a quadrangular shape. The statue of Mahishasura is a prominent feature. During the reign of the Wadiyars of Mysore, the Maharaja rode on an elephant in the golden howdah during the Vijayadashami (tenth day of Dasara) procession. Following independence, an idol of Chamundeshwari is taken on a procession during Dasara.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThere are several other lovely sites to visit when you take a tour of Mysore. You can easily take a one-day trip to Mysore and visit new tourist spots each time.',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:42:07','2022-08-20 11:42:07'),(47,5,'FOLLOW YOUR HEART AND HEED TO THE CALLING','Bangalore to wayanad tour package','Even though the weather in Wayanad travel is lovely all year, the ideal time to come is between October and May. The temperature is controlled by the town\'s elevation.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIf you are looking for travel info on Wayanad, the temperature in Wayanad ranges between 20 - 30 degrees Celsius, with a mild breeze blowing through the area due to the evergreen forest cover but experiencing heat from March to May.\r\n<br><br>\r\nWayanad is derived from the Malayalam word \'Vayal Naadu,\' which translates to the land of paddy fields in English.\r\n<br><br>\r\nIf you are considering a trip to Kerala, you cannot afford to overlook a one-day trip package or 2 days trip to the Wayanad district, which is home to numerous stunning tourist sites.\r\n<br><br>\r\n Wayanad tour packages with prices are easily accessible online on the website of Tejas Travels. \r\n<br><br>\r\nTravel to Wayanad from Bangalore on a tour package and take an unforgettable 1-day trip. \r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nEDDAKAL CAVES\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe Edakkal Caves are one of the must-see attractions in Wayanad 4000 ft. above sea level. These are two caves accessible through a hike up the Ambukutty Mala (Hill). It is home to stone-age engravings, which are estimated to be over 6000 years old. The engravings provide a look into our prehistoric existence.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe first cave isn\'t particularly interesting, but the second cave contains numerous rock sculptures on the walls of human figures, animals and weapon forms.\r\n<br><br>\r\nLAKKADI VIEWPOINT\r\n<br><br>\r\nLakkidi View Point leads you around the many curves of the mountain road for which it is famous, and the valley from the viewpoint is breathtaking. This viewpoint is located on the Thamarassery Ghat pass, which runs across the majestic mountains. Vythiri is the nearest town situated at a distance of 5 km. \r\n<br><br>\r\nSOOCHIPAARA FALLS\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe waterfall is roughly 200 metres high and reveals the rock wall. Sentinel Rock Waterfalls, located in Wayanad\'s Vellarimala district, feels like watching angel-like falls. The water is pure and gives you a cloud-like or smooth fabric feel. Soochipara, the name suggests rock climbing. The beautiful water flows into the Chaliyar River.\r\n<br><br>\r\nTHOLPETTY WILDLIFE SANCTUARY\r\n<br><br>\r\nTholpetty Species Sanctuary is nestled in the lap of Wayanad and the Western Ghats and is famous for the diversity of wildlife that can be seen here like elephants, tigers, leopards, bears, deer, monkeys, reptiles, fishes, and bird species living in their natural habitat. The timings are from 7 am to 10 am and 3 pm to 5 pm.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nKURUMBALAKOTTA\r\n<br><br>\r\nKurumbalakkotta is a tiny hamlet in Kalpetta, Kerala\'s Wayanad District. It was supposed to be the Fort of a Kurumbapaalakan (meaning a monarch). \r\nYou may begin your adventure in Malakara. As you near the summit, you can see numerous other tall peaks in the distance. The subtropical savannahs, gorgeous hills, enormous spice plantations, and lush woods may all be seen from here providing spectacular views.  The Panamaram River may be seen from Kurumbalakkotta, flowing like a silvery cincture. \r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nCHEENGERI MALA\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe stone is generally hurled in the shape of an apparition skull and is therefore known as Phantom Rock around the world. The picturesque location is 26 kilometres from Kalpetta. Cheengeri Mala, like other places in Wayanad, is a popular destination for hikers and adventurers. The beautiful rock stands tall at a height of 2600 metres above sea level and is surrounded by lush foliage; it\'s a perfect location for anyone seeking quiet and tranquillity.\r\n<br><br>\r\nCHEMBRA PEAK\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Chembra is considered to be the highest point in Wayanad, standing at 2100 metres above sea level. It is the ideal tourist destination for nature enthusiasts to admire its beauty and offers challenging hikes for brave hearts. The natural heart-shaped lake atop the hill is visible from practically every region of Wayanad, and it is the main attraction. Trek charges range from Rs 20 to 30 for one person. If you are trekking as a group then the price may range anywhere from Rs 750 to Rs 1500. Charges for parking and cameras apply separately. Goddess Sita, according to legend, bathed in the Chembra Peak lake. This lake is also reported to have never dried up.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nBANASURA SAGAR DAM\r\n<br><br>\r\nThis dam is one of the most photographed tourist attractions in Wayanad. Banasura Dam, the second largest of its sort in Asia, is a notable location to visit in Wayanad. It is situated in the Western Ghats, approximately 21 kilometres from Kalpetta. The picturesque view of mountain folds that lays in the backdrop of the dam, located at the foothills of Banasura, is one of nature\'s tranquil wonders.\r\n\r\nWayanad is one of the most exotic places in South India. It is also a popular Honeymoon destination. It is a well-maintained place which has gone through certain changes due to the recent floods. Let us support them. \r\n\r\nMYSORE - THE IMPERIAL LAND OF KINGS\r\n\r\nThe city of Mysore is indeed a paradise for all kinds of travellers. Mysore tourism has seen a sunset for years now because of the places to visit near Mysore\r\n\r\nHire the Mysore tours and travels services at Tejas Travels as your own Mysore travel agency.',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:42:34','2022-08-20 11:42:34'),(48,4,'Adventurous Trail At the Unparalleled City Of Alleppey','Alleppey tour packages','Alleppey, commonly known as Alappuzha, is a city famous for several calm and serene backwaters and traditional houseboats.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAlappuzha tourism’s vitality is provided by the vast backwaters of canals, lagoons, and lakes.\r\n<br><br>\r\nDuring the harvest season, the snake boat race in the backwaters witnessed big crowds coming from all around the world to their delight. The exhilaration of boat racing is truly incredible. You could choose the Alappuzha one-day tour package to behold this event.\r\n<br><br>\r\nFor Munnar Alleppey tour packages for 3 days begin with a cruise to discover this land\'s natural splendour. You never spend a day idle if you book Alappuzha tourism packages. \r\n<br><br>\r\nAlleppey one-day tour packages, Cochin Alleppey tour packages, Bangalore to Alleppey tour packages, and Alleppey tour packages from Hyderabad are all available at a reasonable price.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nUnravel The Nature’s Gift In God’s Own Country\r\n  <br><br>\r\nAlappuzha Beach\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe lovely Alleppey Beach has a 140-year-old pier that stretches into the sea. It is home to the sand art festival regularly observed at Alleppey. Alappuzha\'s one-day tourism packages are generally in demand. People generally wish to take Bangalore To Alleppey Tour packages, Cochin to Alleppey Tour Packages, Alleppey tour packages From Hyderabad, Munnar to Alleppey tour packages and Alapuzzha one-day tour packages just to visit the Alappuzha Beach.\r\n <br><br>\r\n \r\nMullackal\r\n<br><br>\r\nMullackal is a Konkani Brahmin village where the  Bhagavathy Temple is located. The people who live here specialise in preparing delectable sweets. Chirappu, is the primary festival here and at Mariamman temple located at a distance from here. A fair is held around this time to showcase vessels and other artefacts available for merchandise.\r\n<br><br>\r\nKuttanad Backwaters\r\n<br><br>\r\nKuttanad Backwaters is indeed an experience, not just a location. It is a magnificent lagoon surrounded by lakes, rivers, canals, foggy mountains, and ethereal sceneries. The sensation of cruising around the gorgeous backwaters on a houseboat is indescribable. To add to the glory find beautiful paddy fields, the area is also known as the \"Rice Bowl of Kerala.\" Even if you book a one-day Alleppey houseboat tour package, this should be your complete agenda.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSt. Mary\'s Forane Church\r\n<br><br>\r\nEvery year, the church arranges two feasts or festivals. The first is the Feast of St. Mary every year on the third Sunday of September. On this day, people attend mass and participate in the celebration, donning distinctive costumes for the parade and mass.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe Feast of St. Sebastian is also observed here. Fireworks and other colourful displays make this feast memorable, intriguing, and enjoyable. The church\'s beautiful decorations, feast, and imperial architecture make it one of the top sites to visit in Alleppey.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAlleppey Lighthouse\r\n<br><br>\r\nAlleppey or Alappuzha lighthouse, located around 4 kilometres ahead of Alappuzha town, provides a spectacular 360-degree view of the ocean as well as the territorial area of Alleppey, which is mostly dense and lush forest. The hours are from 3 p.m. to 5 p.m., and there is a small admission fee.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMarari Beach\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe crown of the Malabar Coast, The Marari Beach is famous for fishing and local cuisine available at the thriving restaurants. The National Geographic Survey ranks it as one of the top hammock beaches in the world. The glistening sands, the clear blue skies and the aroma of the local cuisine with the typical fragrance of the beach are truly mesmerising.\r\n <br><br>\r\n \r\nVembanad Lake\r\n<br><br>\r\nVembanad Lake is Kerala’s longest lake and is also among the largest in India with an area of 2033 square kilometres and a maximum length of 96.5 kilometres. It has also been recognized under the National Wetlands Conservation Programme. The official name of the lake is Vembanad-Kol Wetland.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAlleppey is a must-see place that has been carefully designed by God to show the marvel of His craftsmanship. Plan excursions to Alleppey to create unforgettable memories of breathtaking landscapes, the sound of rushing streams, waves, and the gorgeous horizon.',NULL,'2022-08-20 11:42:53','2022-08-20 11:42:53');
